{"items":[{"full_name":"Localization","formal_statement":"abbrev Localization := OreLocalization S M","informal_statement":"The localization of a commutative monoid $M$ at a submonoid $S$ is the quotient of $M \times S$ by the congruence relation $\sim$ where $(x_1, y_1) \sim (x_2, y_2)$ if and only if there exists $c \in S$ such that $c \cdot (y_2 \cdot x_1) = c \cdot (x_2 \cdot y_1)$. This construction satisfies the universal property of localizations, where elements of $S$ become invertible in the localization."},{"full_name":"Localization.Away","formal_statement":"/-- Given `x : M`, the Localization of `M` at the Submonoid generated by `x`, as a quotient. -/
